{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"4072","heading":"Definitions","label":"4072 Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/ch52/schVIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs4072","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs4072%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “secondary school” means a public school which provides secondary education as determined by State law.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs4072%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “sponsorship” includes the act of promoting, leading, or participating in a meeting. The assignment of a teacher, administrator, or other school employee to a meeting for custodial purposes does not constitute sponsorship of the meeting.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs4072%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “meeting” includes those activities of student groups which are permitted under a school’s limited open forum and are not directly related to the school curriculum.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs4072%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “noninstructional time” means time set aside by the school before actual classroom instruction begins or after actual classroom instruction ends.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
